The majority of women in Fiji simply cannot have the time and fulfil other responsibilities while they are pregnant and raising children. The rich/lucky women can afford to have private hospital procedures while women from marginalised communities and villagers are resorting to unsafe practices where death or permanent disability is all too frequent. Until 2013, Fiji relied on a predominantly male board and senior personnel at the Fiji Family Planning Association (FFPA) who refused to accept and revise the stance on abortion despite the country hanging around the lowest in the world population statistics. It is an urgent issue to be addressed and women should not have to suffer from the process.

The mission of the Fiji Family Planning Association is to empower every person through free and voluntary family planning, gender equality and sexual and reproductive health rights to improve lives and achieve a world with no gender inequality.Fiji Family Planning Association are the largest provider of a full range of modern contraceptives, they provide affordable, accessible and comprehensive quality sexual health care services including, provision of clinical services, training, advocacy on gender and poverty concerns, and awareness-raising and education campaigns in Fiji.
